/=  *  /common/zeke
/=  *  /common/test
=<
|%
++  test-cheetah-add
  %+  expect-eq  !>(%.y)
  !>
  %+  roll  cheetah-add-kats
  |=  [tv=cheetah-add-tv acc=?]
  ?&  acc
    ::
      .=  [(list-to-f6lt:cheetah sumx.tv) (list-to-f6lt:cheetah sumy.tv) %.n]
      %+  ch-add:affine:curve:cheetah
        [(list-to-f6lt:cheetah px.tv) (list-to-f6lt:cheetah py.tv) %.n]
      [(list-to-f6lt:cheetah qx.tv) (list-to-f6lt:cheetah qy.tv) %.n]
  ==
::
++  test-cheetah-varbase-mul
  %+  expect-eq  !>(%.y)
  !>
  %+  roll  cheetah-varbase-mul-kats
  |=  [tv=cheetah-varbase-mul-tv acc=?]
  ?&  acc
    ::
      .=  [(list-to-f6lt:cheetah prodx.tv) (list-to-f6lt:cheetah prody.tv) %.n]
      %+  ch-scal:affine:curve:cheetah  scalar.tv
    [(list-to-f6lt:cheetah px.tv) (list-to-f6lt:cheetah py.tv) %.n]
  ==
::
++  test-cheetah-fixbase-mul
  %+  expect-eq  !>(%.y)
  !>
  %+  roll  cheetah-fixbase-mul-kats
  |=  [tv=cheetah-fixbase-mul-tv acc=?]
  ?&  acc
    ::
      .=  [(list-to-f6lt:cheetah prodx.tv) (list-to-f6lt:cheetah prody.tv) %.n]
      (ch-scal:affine:curve:cheetah scalar.tv a-gen:curve:cheetah)
  ==
--
::
|%
:: The cheetah-add-tv type defines addition test vectors. Let
::    * P be the Cheetah point with affine coordinates (px, py)
::    * Q be the Cheetah point with affine coordinates (qx, qy)
::    * R be the Cheetah point with affine coordinates (sumx, sumy)
::  then these test vectors have the property that P + Q = R.
::  The vectors are defined in this file under the name cheetah-add-kats
+$  cheetah-add-tv  [px=(list @) py=(list @) qx=(list @) qy=(list @) sumx=(list @) sumy=(list @)]

:: The cheetah-varbase-mul-tv type defines variable-base scalar multiplication test vectors. Let
::    * P be the Cheetah point with affine coordinates (px, py)
::    * s be an element of the scalar field with integer representation `scalar`
::    * R be the Cheetah point with affine coordinates (prodx, prody)
::  then these test vectors have the property that sP = R.
::  The vectors are defined in this file under the name cheetah-varbase-mul-kats
+$  cheetah-varbase-mul-tv  [px=(list @) py=(list @) scalar=@ prodx=(list @) prody=(list @)]

:: The cheetah-fixbase-mul-tv type defines fixed-base scalar multiplication test vectors. Let
::    * s be an element of the scalar field with integer representation `scalar`
::    * R be the Cheetah point with affine coordinates (prodx, prody)
::  then these test vectors have the property that sG = R, where G is the Cheetah generator.
::  The vectors are defined in this file under the name cheetah-fixbase-mul-kats
+$  cheetah-fixbase-mul-tv  [scalar=@ prodx=(list @) prody=(list @)]

